UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1556
1 A JOINT RESOLUTION declaring Kentucky a Food is Medicine state and
2 directing state agencies to advance Food is Medicine initiatives.
3 WHEREAS, the United States spends $4.5 trillion annually on health care with 90
4 percent of those expenditures covering care for people with chronic physical and mental
5 health conditions; and
6 WHEREAS, six in 10 Americans have at least one chronic condition and four in 10
7 have two or more chronic conditions; and
8 WHEREAS, diet-related physical conditions such as obesity impact 41.9 percent of
9 adults in the United States and result in $173 billion annually in health care costs; and
10 WHEREAS, in Kentucky, 40.4 percent of adults have at least one chronic
11 reversable physical condition such as diabetes or heart issues, which results in over $29.4
12 billion in health care expenses annually; and
13 WHEREAS, some state pilot programs and national studies have demonstrated that
14 Food is Medicine intervention programs, especially when administered in clinical
15 settings, can prevent and improve health care outcomes for chronic conditions, thereby
16 reducing chronic condition rates and health care costs; and
17 WHEREAS, Kentucky has pioneered Food is Medicine efforts, including the
18 Kentucky Hospital Association's (KHA) partnership with the Kentucky Department of
19 Agriculture (KDA), to launch a dedicated initiative to integrate health care and
20 agriculture with the goal of making Kentucky citizens healthier by addressing poor
21 nourishment, nutrition insecurity, and agriculture production barriers as well as health
22 insurance provisions, basic nutrition needs, and chronic condition management; and
23 WHEREAS, Kentucky hospitals, through the KHA and its members, are leading in
24 the Food is Medicine initiative by creating and implementing Food is Medicine programs
25 in clinical settings and employee care programs that track and monitor health outcomes;
26 and
27 WHEREAS, declaring Kentucky a Food is Medicine state will build on the
Page 1 of 2
