UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1556
1 foundations of the KHA and the KDA partnership by fostering collaboration among
2 health care providers, private insurers, managed care organizations, state agencies, local
3 governments, and nonprofit organizations to expand initiatives using local farm products
4 in nutritional health interventions; and
5 WHEREAS, the Food is Medicine state declaration aligns with Kentucky's
6 commitment to improving population health, reducing health disparities, and promoting
7 preventive care as cost-effective strategies for long-term fiscal sustainability, particularly
8 amid Kentucky's ongoing battle against nourishment and nutrition-sensitive chronic
9 conditions;
10 NOW, THEREFORE,
11 Be it resolved by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
12 Section 1. The General Assembly hereby declares Kentucky to be a Food is
13 Medicine state to recognize the critical role of nutrition in preventing and managing
14 chronic conditions and to promote the use of local food products in health care systems.
15 Section 2. State agencies are directed to advance Food is Medicine initiatives
16 by taking all appropriate actions, including but not limited to:
17 (1) Affirming the integration of nutrition as a core component of medical treatment and
18 public health policy;
19 (2) Supporting coordination with the Kentucky Hospital Association, the Kentucky
20 Department of Agriculture, and other relevant agencies and partners to pilot
21 medically tailored meals and produce prescriptions for high-risk populations;
22 (3) Forming public-private partnerships to support local food systems and community-
23 based food delivery; and
24 (4) Supporting evaluations to measure the health outcomes, cost savings, and equity
25 impacts of Food is Medicine initiatives.
